Do not trust current Q posts. Nothing against you Jeff but understand the Skepticism about Q because as an IT Guy, I know how effortless it is to corrupt data–and with my limited understanding of counterintelligence methods, I understand that bad actors are very sophisticated at generating confusion.
If you think “Shadow Banning” folks is terrible, think about this: You post a message on a digital board; you can effortlessly see what you have posted on your screen and what others are stating in reply. Nevertheless, a third party intercepts and changes your message as it gets sent out to others–suddenly the message they get reads OPPOSITE what you sent. Then they respond back–again the third party changes their reply to fit your original message.
What is occurring here? You end up having two fabricated conversations. Each person believes they are talking to the other, when in truth they are talking to a third party. The same could occur with Q. This is a very real threat when your only interaction is through a digital apparatus. Keep that in mind as you go online. Always retain a healthy dose of skepticism.
